OL,7,F"The spectacle of the battle between
OL,8,Fthe Post Office chief executive and
OL,9,Fits former chairman light up a simple
OL,10,Ftruth; that the top of the Post Office
OL,11,Fis in utter disarray and not fit for
OL,12,Fpurpose to run the payouts to former
OL,13,Fsub-postmasters."
OL,15,FThere had also been a public row
OL,16,Fbetween Mr Staunton and Ms Badenoch,
OL,17,Fafter he alleged he was told by a
OL,18,Fsenior civil servant to stall on
OL,19,Fcompensation claims ahead of the
OL,20,Felection.
